4345	  With \(j\) the composite immersion of \cref{def:composite_basic_open_immersion}, let
4346	  \(\sigma = \mathrm{gammaImageRingEquiv}\,j\,\top : \Gamma(\mathcal{O}_{\Spec R_s}, \top) \xrightarrow{\sim}
4347	  \Gamma(\mathcal{O}_{\Spec R}, j\,''^{U}\top)\) be the \(\top\)-level structure-sheaf ring iso
4348	  (\cref{def:gamma_image_ring_equiv}), and put \(f' := \sigma^{-1}(\mathrm{algebraMap}\,R\,R_s\,f)\). Then
4349	  \[
4350	    \sigma(f') = \mathrm{algebraMap}\,R\,R_s\,f, \qquad j\,''^{U}\,D(f') = D(f) \sqcap D(s) .
4351	  \]
4352	\end{lemma}
4353	\begin{proof}
4354	  \uses{lem:composite_immersion_range_basicOpen, def:gamma_image_ring_equiv}
4355	  The identity \(\sigma(f') = \mathrm{algebraMap}\,R\,R_s\,f\) is definitional from
4356	  \(f' = \sigma^{-1}(\mathrm{algebraMap}\,R\,R_s\,f)\). For the image: \(j\) carries the basic open
4357	  \(D(f')\) to the basic open of \(\sigma(f') = \mathrm{algebraMap}\,R\,R_s\,f\) intersected with the
4358	  range \(j.\mathrm{opensRange} = D(s)\) (\cref{lem:composite_immersion_range_basicOpen}); since the image
4359	  of \(f\) cuts out \(D(f)\), this is \(D(f) \sqcap D(s)\).

